parish church of St Peter (Diocese of Winchester) anchors the southern end of the village; Victorian restorations are visible. Archaeology runs deep: flint mines in the parish date to roughly 3,983 BC, and the Quarley High Linear earthwork to around 245 BC. The Wallops share two pubs, a village hall, a Good village primary at Nether Wallop, a veterinary surgery and a shop with post office. Over Wallop has its own Conservation Area designation and an active Neighbourhood Development Plan (adopted 2022) focused on resisting excessive housing development.","character":"Loose linear village along chalk lanes with timber-framed and brick-and-flint cottages, plus a number of 20th-century additions. Working agricultural village rather than show village; population around 1,000 across the parish. The Brook frames the conservation area and is the social spine.","amenities":["St Peter''s Church (12th century)","The White Hart (Over Wallop village pub)","Wallops shop with Post Office (Nether Wallop)","Wallops Parish Hall (Middle Wallop)","Veterinary surgery (shared Wallops)","Cricket club","Active Neighbourhood Development Plan","Wallop Brook source (parish)"],"schools":[{"name":"Wallop Primary School (Nether Wallop)","phase":"Primary","ofsted":"Good","distance":"1.5 mi","url":"https://files.ofsted.gov.uk/v1/file/50221039"},{"name":"Test Valley School / Danebury School, Stockbridge","phase":"Secondary","ofsted":"Inadequate (2022)","distance":"6.5 mi","url":"https://reports.ofsted.gov.uk/"}],"transport":{"commutes":[{"to":"London Waterloo (via Grateley)","time":"~1h 20m","mode":"drive + train (SWR West of England line)","source":"https://www.nationalrail.co.uk/"},{"to":"London Waterloo (via Andover, fastest)","time":"1h 2m","mode":"drive + train","source":"https://www.thetrainline.com/train-times/andover-to-london-waterloo"},{"to":"Salisbury","time":"~25m","mode":"drive (A343 / A30)","source":"https://www.nationalrail.co.uk/"}],"nearestStation":"Grateley (3.0 mi)","roads":"A343 ~1 mi; A30 (Stockbridge) ~5 mi; A303 ~3 mi"},"prices":{"avgSold12Mo":null,"avgDetached":null,"avgSemi":null,"avgTerraced":null,"avgFlat":null,"source":"https://www.rightmove.co.uk/house-prices/so20.html","asOf":"2026-05"},"thingsToDo":["Walking the Wallop Brook Way (4.7-mile route)","St Peter''s Church visit","Quarley High Linear earthwork (~2 mi)","Army Flying Museum (1.5 mi at Middle Wallop)","Salisbury cathedral and market (12 mi)","Annual Over Wallop village fête"],"placesToEat":[{"name":"The White Hart, Over Wallop","type":"Village pub","notes":"Traditional Wallops freehouse with food","url":"https://www.useyourlocal.com/"},{"name":"The George Inn, Middle Wallop","type":"Village pub","notes":"1.5 mi east in Middle Wallop","url":"https://www.useyourlocal.com/"}],"pros":["Wallop Primary (Good) shared across all three Wallops villages","Quietest of the Wallops — furthest from the A343 and AAC airfield noise","Grateley station 3 mi for Waterloo trains via SWR West of England line","Strong neighbourhood plan protecting rural character"],"cons":["Wiltshire-border position means some council services are split with Wiltshire CC","Secondary catchment school rated Inadequate in 2022","AAC airfield helicopter noise audible across the parish","Limited evening transport; pub closure or shop turnover hurts daily life"],"whoItSuits":"Buyers wanting the chalk-stream Test Valley character at slightly lower prices than Stockbridge proper, with a Good village primary and decent train access via either Grateley or Andover. Quieter than Middle Wallop because further from the airfield, but the helicopters are still audible. Best fit for families with primary-age children, service-family households on Middle Wallop posting wanting some buffer from the airfield, and downsizers from Stockbridge or Salisbury. The Wiltshire-border position means some practical services (utility providers, county-specific schemes) need cross-county checks.","broadbandMedianMbps":null,"nearestStation":"Grateley (3.0 mi)","primarySupermarket":"Waitrose, Stockbridge (5.0 mi); Sainsbury''s, Andover (7.0 mi)","images":[],"sources":["https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Over_Wallop","https://over-wallop.parish.uk/","https://www.british-history.ac.uk/vch/hants/vol4/pp530-535","https://hwwhite.co.uk/salisbury/the-wallops/","https://owparishndp.uk/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/History-part-1-2.pdf","https://files.ofsted.gov.uk/v1/file/50221039","https://www.thetrainline.com/train-times/andover-to-london-waterloo","https://www.testvalley.gov.uk/benefitsandcounciltax/counciltax/council-tax-charges"]},{"id":"ovington-so24","name":"Ovington","village":"Ovington","town":"Winchester","county":"Hampshire","postcode":"SO24","hubCity":"Southampton","regionDir":"North","settlementType":"Non-City","subRegion":"Winchester","coords":{"lat":51.08712,"lng":-1.17352},"coordsSource":"postcode-outward-approx","houseTypeIds":[],"status":"directory","priceSummary":null,"councilTaxBand":null,"overview":"","character":"","amenities":[],"schools":[],"transport":{"commutes":[]},"prices":{},"thingsToDo":[],"placesToEat":[],"pros":[],"cons":[],"whoItSuits":[],"broadbandMedianMbps":null,"nearestStation":null,"primarySupermarket":null,"images":[],"sources":[]},{"id":"owlsbury-so21","name":"Owlsbury","village":"Owlsbury","town":"Winchester","county":"Hampshire","postcode":"SO21","hubCity":"Southampton","regionDir":"North","settlementType":"Non-City","subRegion":"Winchester","coords":{"lat":51.08284,"lng":-1.31848},"coordsSource":"postcode-outward-approx","houseTypeIds":[],"status":"directory","priceSummary":null,"councilTaxBand":null,"overview":"","character":"","amenities":[],"schools":[],"transport":{"commutes":[]},"prices":{},"thingsToDo":[],"placesToEat":[],"pros":[],"cons":[],"whoItSuits":[],"broadbandMedianMbps":null,"nearestStation":null,"primarySupermarket":null,"images":[],"sources":[]}]'::jsonb) AS value;

